            <arrangement id="aspace_a9c339410341c2b88de522fce0548a2e">
               <head>Arrangement</head>
               <p>Arranged alphabetically by business type. The number in parentheses following each file title indicates the number of licenses present for that business type.</p>
            </arrangement>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_b01d89481488245eb95d8c8982179309">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Circa 1,025 printed licenses for businesses and individuals in Montana Territory including assayers, attorneys, brewers, butchers, dance houses, doctors, gambling houses and saloons, hotels, inns and taverns, merchants, ranchers, saloons, and theaters. Other licenses document auctioneers, jewelers, bankers, liveries and stables, branding houses, and other establishments, occupations, or trades. Circa 525 miscellaneous licenses note the individual to whom the license was issued, its duration, the fee, the locality, and the name of the collector--they do not, however, record a specific occupation or trade.</p>
               <p>Included is a booklet of licenses exclusively for businesses and individuals in Fort Benton.</p>
            </scopecontent>
